  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Contracts Manager (M&E)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To prepare documentation for tender submissions.</li>\n  <li>To develop tender strategies and oversee tender estimation responsibilities.</li>\n  <li>To coordinate with all parties to provide accurate analysis of the participated project, including collating critical information and preparing final submission documentation.</li>\n  <li>To lead and monitor the QS team for variation works, progress claims, and cost control.</li>\n  <li>To develop and improve departmental workflow and productivity.</li>\n  <li>To liaise with main contractors, subcontractors, clients, and</li>\n  <li>suppliers/vendors for project claims and cost issues.</li>\n  <li>To develop standards for contracts, including the presentation of budgets, payment terms, etc.</li>\n  <li>To review the contractual performance of all parties to ensure compliance with terms and conditions.</li>\n  <li>To periodically report work progress to senior management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<p>Diploma or Degree in Construction Management/Building /Quantity Surveying.</p>\n<p>Knowledge of tender experience will be considered.</p>\n<p>Minimum 5-years of relevant working experience in the Construction industry.</p>\n<p>Meticulous and systematic individual with positive working attitude.</p>\n<p>Good oral &amp; written communication skills.</p>\n<p>Multi-tasking and is able to handle stress.</p>",
